This directory contains structured traversal mechanisms used to generate and evaluate recurring conflicts through repeated multi-agent passes over the same contradiction.

Traversal outputs are treated as provisional signals and isolated from core BELLA mechanics until sufficient recurrence demonstrates semantic validity.

Typical contents include:

TraversalRecord schemas
Quarantine and promotion logic for traversal-generated conflicts
Demotion and replay rules
Instrumentation for measuring convergence and recurrence behavior

Goal:

Provide a controlled method for introducing structured disagreement into BELLA while preventing transient role-structure artifacts from contaminating long-term belief dynamics.
